2Famp_articleshow%2F103883887.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20the%20Big%20Man%E2%80%99s%20Departure%2C%20the%20Debris%20of%20His%20Destruction%20Lies%20Everywhere%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01150618%2FC48CE12B-72F4-4594-98C6-DDD5E2178AF8_1_105_c.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20page%2087%20of%20his%20new%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EAfter%20Messiah%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Aakar%20Patel%20writes%20a%20short%20essay%20on%20how%20the%20office%20of%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20republic%2C%20whom%20he%20only%20names%20Big%20Man%2C%20has%20changed%20dramatically%20since%20he%20first%20took%20over.%20The%20office%20now%20dominates%20the%20government%3B%20ministers%20have%20no%20decision-making%20power%20and%20ministries%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%9Cdelivering%20the%20finest%20possible%20event%20or%20ceremony%20the%20Big%20Man%20could%20preside%20over%E2%80%9D.%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20book%20may%20begin%20after%20the%20Big%20Man%20is%20gone%2C%20but%20the%20debris%20of%20his%20destruction%20is%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20193px)%2085vw%2C%20193px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23115733%2Fimage-1342-193x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22193%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23115733%2Fimage-1342-193x300.png%20193w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F23115733%2Fimage-1342.png%20401w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674466%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAfter%20Messiah%20by%20Aakar%20Patel.%20(Vintage%20Books%2C%20September%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20describes%20the%20charismatic%20leader%E2%80%99s%20government%20as%20not%20very%20different%20from%20a%20kingdom%20and%20his%20blistering%20critique%20of%20the%20new%20avatar%20of%20the%20republic%20sums%20up%20the%20present%20moment%20perfectly%3A%20regular%20raids%20on%20dissenters%20and%20opposition%3B%20a%20servile%20media%3B%20a%20ruler%20speaking%20of%20himself%20in%20the%20third%20person%3B%20social%20media%20accounts%20of%20elected%20representatives%20run%20only%20by%20the%20PMO%20(the%20action%20unfolds%20in%20the%20PMO%20though%20the%20author%20steers%20clear%20of%20the%20title%20Prime%20Minister)%3B%20a%20sidelined%20old%20guard%3B%20a%20right%20hand%20man%20who%20does%20the%20Big%20Man%E2%80%99s%20dirty%20work%3B%20key%20government%20data%20that%20is%20not%20released%20or%20even%20gathered%3B%20the%20ignoring%20of%20joblessness%20and%20other%20bad%20news%3B%20and%20the%20punishments%20for%20those%20who%20make%20the%20mistake%20of%20sharing%20any%20such%20worrying%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20tackling%20the%20past%20and%20the%20present%20in%20his%20previous%20books%2C%20Patel%20has%20moved%20to%20the%20future.%20%3Cem%3EAfter%20Messiah%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20satirical%2C%20fictional%20take%20on%20our%20future.%20The%20most%20powerful%20parts%20of%20this%20novel%20though%2C%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20you%20and%20I%20wish%20were%20fiction%20but%20know%20otherwise.%20Like%20the%20essay%20that%20begins%20on%20page%2087.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20fourth%20book%20in%20four%20years%20%E2%80%93%202020%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EOur%20Hindu%20Rashtra%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20a%20look%20at%20the%20history%20of%20our%20majoritarian%20state%20and%20how%20we%20accelerated%20to%20the%20present-day%20Hindutva.%20His%20second%2C%202021%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Price%20of%20The%20Modi%20Years%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20a%20data%20and%20fact%20driven%20report%20card%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Anarchist%20Cookbook%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%202022%20gave%20readers%20the%20ingredients%20and%20the%20recipe%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbake%20your%20own%20campaign%20for%20change%E2%80%9D.%20And%20now%20%3Cem%3EAfter%20Messiah%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20work%20of%20fiction%20that%20feels%20very%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Patel%E2%80%99s%20latest%2C%20a%20dramatic%20physical%20fight%20between%20politicians%20may%20remind%20you%20of%20televised%20battles%20in%20parliament%20and%20how%20democracy%20is%20increasingly%20a%20farce.%20There%E2%80%99s%20resort%20politics%20and%20philosophical%20musings%20on%20whether%20the%20state%20can%20be%20anything%20other%20than%20violent%20and%20how%20humane%20leaders%20should%20tackle%20dissent.%20No%20real%20novel%20of%20our%20times%20can%20be%20complete%20without%20preventive%20detention%2C%20but%20this%20law%20plays%20a%20supporting%20role%20to%20the%20Land%20Acquisition%20Act.%20Plus%20there%E2%80%99s%20music%20and%20humour%20because%20this%20is%20Patel%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIs%20the%20author%20trying%20to%20tell%20us%20that%20any%20political%20option%20is%20better%3F%20Or%20is%20he%20saying%20the%20system%20won%E2%80%99t%20let%20anyone%20do%20better%3F%20You%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20read%20the%20book%20to%20find%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%20now%20I%E2%80%99ve%20said%20that%20political%20satirists%20have%20the%20unenviable%20task%20of%20competing%20with%20the%20everyday%20outrageous%20reality%20of%20India.%20Patel%20sets%20himself%20up%20for%20this%20impossible%20task%20and%20succeeds.%20He%C2%A0%20does%20this%20by%20not%20competing%20with%20reality%2C%20instead%20he%20imagines%20a%20future%20scenario%20and%20sets%20it%20in%20present-day%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPatel%20was%20always%20a%20writer.%20Now%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20fighting%20multiple%20battles%20against%20the%20state%20machinery%2C%20he%20is%20paying%20the%20price%20of%20the%20Modi%20years%20by%20turning%20into%20a%20compulsive%20%3Cem%3Esutradhaar%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eunable%20to%20take%20his%20eyes%20off%20a%20nation%20on%20a%20rampage.%20With%20every%20new%20work%2C%20the%20author%20uses%20a%20different%20format%2C%20maybe%20because%20he%20wants%20to%20try%20everything%20to%20get%20through%20to%20you%20or%20maybe%20because%20he%20finds%20it%20boring%20to%20not%20keep%20reinventing%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20yes%2C%20his%20next%20work%20is%20a%20screenplay.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpriyaramani.substack.com%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPriya%20Ramani%E2%80%99s%20Substack.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695450744000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01150618%2FC48CE12B-72F4-4594-98C6-DDD5E2178AF8_1_105_c.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Faakar-patels-new-work-of-fiction-feels-very-real%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20author%20describes%20the%20charismatic%20leader%E2%80%99s%20government%20as%20not%20very%20different%20from%20a%20kingdom%20and%20his%20blistering%20critique%20of%20the%20new%20avatar%20of%20the%20republic%20sums%20up%20the%20present%20moment%20perfectly%3A%20regular%20raids%2C%3B%20a%20servile%20media%3B%20a%20ruler%20speaking%20of%20himself%20in%20the%20third%20person%2C%20and%20other%20bad%20news.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Faakar-patels-new-work-of-fiction-feels-very-real%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Top%20X%20boss%20in%20India%20'resigns'%20-%20amid%20court%20battle%20over%20content%20removal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695450720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F09%2F768x432%2Fskynews-twitter-x-logo_6294839.jpg%3F20230923083302%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsamiran-gupta-top-x-twitter-boss-in-india-resigns-amid-court-battle-over-content-removal-12967750%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Social%20media%20platform%20X's%20most%20senior%20employee%20in%20India%20has%20resigned%20ahead%20of%20the%20country's%20elections%2C%20as%20the%20company%20fights%20the%20government%20in%20court%20over%20content%20removal%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Reuters%20news%20agency.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsamiran-gupta-top-x-twitter-boss-in-india-resigns-amid-court-battle-over-content-removal-12967750%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsamiran-gupta-top-x-twitter-boss-in-india-resigns-amid-court-battle-over-content-removal-12967750%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsamiran-gupta-top-x-twitter-boss-in-india-resigns-amid-court-battle-over-content-removal-12967750%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22G20%20Called%20for%20'Gender-Inclusive%20Climate%20Action'.%20Is%20it%20Another%20Empty%20Rhetoric%20in%20India's%20Context%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F14170157%2FUntitled-design-2022-06-14T170144.575.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unwomen.org%2Fen%2Fnews-stories%2Fpress-release%2F2023%2F09%2Fpress-release-the-world-is-failing-girls-and-women-according-to-new-un-report%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20UN%20Women%20paints%20a%20worrisome%20global%20picture%20of%20the%20progress%20on%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20pertaining%20to%20gender%20equality.%20Among%20several%20concerns%20raised%2C%20the%20report%20predicts%20that%20going%20by%20the%20current%20trends%20of%20progress%2C%20by%202030%2C%20nearly%208%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20female%20population%20will%20live%20in%20extreme%20poverty%20and%20close%20to%20a%20quarter%20will%20experience%20moderate%20to%20severe%20food%20insecurity.%20The%20report%20also%20points%20to%20the%20deeply%20entrenched%20gender%20gap%20in%20leadership%20positions%20and%20in%20the%20uneven%20distribution%20of%20unpaid%20care%20and%20domestic%20work%20between%20men%20and%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20interesting%20feature%20of%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20report%20is%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20sex-disaggregated%20data%20to%20project%20the%20differentiated%20effects%20of%20climate%20change%20on%20gender%2C%20premised%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98worst-case%20climate%20scenario%E2%80%99.%20As%20per%20this%20methodology%2C%20158.3%20million%2C%20i.e.%2016%20million%20more%20women%20and%20girls%2C%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20total%20number%20of%20men%20and%20boys%2C%20will%20be%20pushed%20to%20poverty%20by%20mid-century%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%20It%20is%20also%20projected%20that%20nearly%20236%20million%20more%20women%20and%20girls%20will%20be%20affected%20by%20food%20insecurity.%20Against%20this%20backdrop%2C%20the%20recently%20concluded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fno-real-gain-g20-delhi-declaration-offers-mere-lip-service-to-pressing-global-issues%5C%22%3EG20%20Summit%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%9Cdriving%20gender-inclusive%20climate%20action%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwomen-led-%20development%E2%80%9D%20gains%20significance.%20Amidst%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fg20-reaches-consensus-on-more-power-to-women%2Farticleshow%2F103699696.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Efour%20priority%20areas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20role%20of%20%E2%80%9Cwomen%20and%20girls%20as%20change-makers%20in%20climate%20resilience%20action%E2%80%9D%20has%20been%20emphasised%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Women%20and%20Child%20Development.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-why-many-of-the-delhi-declarations-climate-commitments-are-vague%5C%22%3EG20%3A%20Why%20Many%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20Climate%20Commitments%20Are%20Vague%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20critical%20question%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20to%20ask%20where%20India%20stands%2C%20on%20gender%20inclusivity%20in%20its%20climate%20action%20plans%2C%20given%20that%20it%20has%20been%20eight%20years%20since%20the%20SDG%20goals%20came%20into%20force%20in%202016.%20Is%20the%20commitment%20to%20involve%20women%20just%20an%20empty%20rhetoric%2C%20or%20is%20there%20a%20genuine%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20gender%20dimensions%20of%20climate%20change%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20in%20subsequent%20paragraphs%20will%20elucidate%20how%20climate%20change%20has%20been%20adversely%20affecting%20women%20and%20girls%20in%20India%2C%20and%20what%20policy%20imperatives%20need%20to%20be%20put%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20climate%20change%20disproportionately%20affect%20women%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWomen%20share%20an%20intimate%20and%20complex%20relationship%20with%20their%20local%20natural%20environment.%20Much%20of%20the%20household%20responsibilities%20that%20are%20climate%20sensitive%20such%20as%20collection%20of%20water%2C%20firewood%2C%20and%20fodder%20as%20well%20as%20ensuring%20food%20security%20for%20families%20fall%20on%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBina%20Agarwal%20in%20her%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EGender%20and%20Green%20Governance%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20provides%20a%20poignant%20narrative%20of%20a%20near-landless%20woman%20in%20Uttarakhand%3A%20%E2%80%9COf%20course%20it%20pains%20me%20to%20cut%20a%20green%20branch%2C%20but%20it%20also%20pains%20me%20when%20my%20children%E2%80%99s%20stomachs%20hurt%20if%20there%20is%20no%20firewood%20to%20cook%20them%20a%20meal.%E2%80%9D%20The%20gender%20division%20of%20labour%20within%20households%20imposes%20demands%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20time%20and%20the%20resulting%20drudgery%20of%20long%20hours%20of%20work%20is%20very%20uneven%20between%20men%20and%20women.%C2%A0When%20combined%20with%20fewer%20employment%20opportunities%2C%20poor%20occupational%20mobility%2C%20and%20low%20wages%2C%20women%20are%20rendered%20more%20socially%20and%20economically%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20cite%20an%20example%2C%20the%20social%20practice%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffeminisminindia.com%2F2023%2F06%2F02%2Fwomen-climate-change-gendered-vulnerabilities%2F%5C%22%3EWater%20Wives%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20village%20in%20western%20Maharashtra%20unravels%20the%20burden%20of%20traveling%20long%20distances%20to%20procure%20drinking%20water%20for%20households%2C%20leaving%20little%20time%20to%20complete%20other%20household%20chores.%20This%20led%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20men%20started%20to%20marry%20more%20than%20one%20woman%20to%20ensure%20adequate%20drinking%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20such%20acute%20hardships%20faced%20by%20women%20in%20drinking%20water%20collection%2C%20India%20does%20not%20have%20a%20single%20comprehensive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ceew.in%2Fpublications%2Faccess-to-safe-clean-drinking-water-services-in-rural-india%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20information%20source%20that%20would%20provide%20necessary%20statistics%20on%20all%20aspects%20of%20safe%20drinking%20water%2C%20such%20as%20the%20physical%20accessibility%20to%20the%20source%2C%20the%20reliability%2C%20the%20quality%20and%20the%20quantity%20required%20for%20households.%20While%20India%20has%20made%20tremendous%20progress%20in%20improving%20the%20drinking%20water%20infrastructure%20in%20rural%20areas%20%E2%80%93%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ceew.in%2Fpublications%2Faccess-to-safe-clean-drinking-water-services-in-rural-india%5C%22%3E50%25%20of%20rural%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20having%20a%20tap%20connection%20within%20the%20dwelling%20or%20premises%20%E2%80%93%20not%20enough%20information%20is%20available%20on%20whether%20the%20physical%20infrastructure%20has%20also%20translated%20into%20better%20reliability%20and%20safety%20of%20drinking%20water.%20Such%20statistics%20are%20crucial%20for%20filling%20existing%20gaps%20in%20the%20provision%20of%20clean%20drinking%20water%20in%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20area%20where%20women%20suffer%20from%20the%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%20is%20the%20collection%20of%20fuel%20for%20cooking%20and%20lighting%20purposes.%20Higher%20temperatures%20have%20been%20found%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.unwomen.org%2Ffeatures%2Fwhy-climate-change-matters-women%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccess%2520to%2520clean%2520cooking%2520fuels%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520use%2520of%2520unclean%2520fuels%2Cchallenges%2520to%2520accessing%2520clean%2520fuels.%5C%22%3Elower%20accessibility%20to%20clean%20fuel%20sources%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20their%20effects%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20livelihoods%20and%20incomes.%20The%20use%20of%20unclean%20fuels%20affects%20women%E2%80%99s%20health%20much%20more%20than%20men%20given%20the%20long%20hours%20of%20indoor%20time%20spent%20by%20them%20and%20their%20primary%20role%20in%20cooking.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Flack-of-access-and-awareness-high-costs-bar-the-poor-from-using-lpg-cylinders-finds-study%5C%22%3ELack%20of%20Access%20and%20Awareness%2C%20High%20Costs%20Bar%20the%20Poor%20from%20Using%20LPG%20Cylinders%2C%20Finds%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fceda.ashoka.edu.in%2Fhow-many-indian-households-use-clean-fuel-for-cooking%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520rural%2520areas%252C%2520almost%2520half%2Ctheir%2520primary%2520fuel%2520for%2520cooking.%5C%22%3Ethird%20of%20Indian%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20still%20relying%20on%20firewood%20for%20cooking%20and%20there%20is%20considerable%20variation%20between%20rural%20and%20urban%20households.%20Nearly%2047%25%20of%20rural%20households%20are%20still%20dependent%20on%20firewood%20for%20cooking%20while%20only%206.5%25%20used%20firewood%20in%20urban%20areas.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Flack-of-access-and-awareness-high-costs-bar-the-poor-from-using-lpg-cylinders-finds-study%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20lack%20of%20access%2C%20awareness%20about%20adverse%20health%20impacts%20of%20solid%20fuels%2C%20and%20high%20costs%20of%20acquiring%20LPG%20cylinders%20were%20discouraging%20women%20from%20shifting%20from%20traditional%20cooking%20fuels.%20Without%20addressing%20these%20glitches%2C%20the%20transition%20to%20clean%20energy%20in%20cooking%20fuel%20cannot%20be%20expected%20to%20fully%20materialise%20through%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20(PMJY)%20which%20aims%20to%20provide%20clean%20fuel%20to%20rural%20and%20low-income%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F06%2FModi-LPG.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-152098%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22483%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFILE%20IMAGE%3A%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20distributes%20the%20free%20LPG%20connections%20to%20the%20beneficiaries%2C%20under%20PM%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20in%20Ballia%20on%20May%201%2C%202016.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FFile%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20relatively%20large%20involvement%20of%20women%20in%20agriculture%20needs%20particular%20mention%20in%20the%20discussion%20of%20climate%20impacts.%20It%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20year%202023%20began%20with%20soaring%20temperatures%20that%20broke%20the%20123-year-old%20record%20in%20February%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20alarming%20proportions%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcsestore.cse.org.in%2Fdefault%2Fbooks%2Fstate-of-india-s-environment-2023-in-figures-ebook.html%5C%22%3EState%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Environment%20in%20Figures%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Science%20and%20Environment%2C%20India%20experienced%20extreme%20weather%20events%20on%2084%20of%20the%20120%20days%20in%20the%20first%20four%20months%20of%202023.%20This%20has%20tremendous%20implications%20for%20agricultural%20yields%20in%20India%20and%20these%20impacts%20can%20cumulatively%20translate%20into%2017%20million%20people%20at%20risk%20of%20hunger%20in%20India%20by%202030%20and%20an%20additional%2016%25%20reduction%20in%20aggregate%20food%20production%20by%202050%20(International%20Food%20Policy%20Research%20Institute%E2%80%99s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifpri.org%2Fpublication%2F2022-global-food-policy-report-climate-change-and-food-systems%5C%22%3EIFPRI%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E).%20This%20creates%20livelihoods%20and%20health-related%20issues%2C%20particularly%20for%20poor%20women%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20regard%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20observe%20that%20women%20constitute%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fagriculture-sector-employs-highest-female-workers-labour-ministry-report-11679929666215.html%5C%22%3E63%25%20of%20the%20agricultural%20%3C%2Fa%3Eworkforce%C2%A0in%20India.%20However%2C%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomen-family-property-inheritence%5C%22%3E7%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20married%20women%20in%20landed%20households%20own%20land.%20Inequality%20in%20land%20rights%20makes%20women%20more%20vulnerable%20while%20also%20reducing%20their%20capacity%20to%20act%20as%20conservers%20of%20land.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adb.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublication%2F453696%2Fewp-559-women-land-title-ownership-empowerment.pdf%5C%22%3EStudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%20that%20women%E2%80%99s%20land%20title%20ownership%20had%20a%20positive%20influence%20on%20their%20ability%20to%20make%20decisions%20regarding%20the%20household%2C%20farming%2C%20and%20livelihood%20activities.%20Innovative%20approaches%20such%20as%20group%20farming%20that%20can%20address%20concerns%20of%20both%20inequality%20in%20access%20to%20land%20as%20well%20as%20the%20issue%20of%20small%20farm%20size%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.orfonline.org%2Fresearch%2Fachieving-gender-equality-in-access-to-land-and-assets%2F%5C%22%3Esuggested%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMGNREGS%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20social%20protection%20and%20climate%20action%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClimate%20disasters%2C%20changing%20weather%2C%20and%20rainfall%20patterns%20have%20disrupted%20rural%20livelihoods%20that%20are%20agriculture-dependent.%20While%20men%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Finterviews%2Fclimate-change%2Fabandonment-poverty-sexual-exploitation-why-indian-women-pay-a-higher-price-for-climate-crisis-80160%5C%22%3Emigrate%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20other%20areas%20for%20non-farm%20work%2C%20women%20end%20up%20bearing%20the%20brunt%20of%20these%20adverse%20climate%20events%20as%20seen%20in%20their%20lower%20food%20consumption%2C%20greater%20indebtedness%2C%20and%20engagement%20in%20low-paid%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnikhil-dey-mgnrega-budget-cut-2023%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Bloodbath%E2%80%99%3A%20Activist%20Nikhil%20Dey%20on%20Budget%20Cuts%20to%20MGNREGA%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESocial%20protection%20programmes%20like%20the%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Scheme%20(MGNREGS)%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fcut-in-mgnregs-harms-women-more-1193938.html%5C%22%3Eattract%20women%20in%20large%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20help%20rural%20households%20and%20economies%20to%20adapt%20to%20climate%20change%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iied.org%2Fenhancing-climate-resilience-impacts-indias-social-protection-programme%5C%22%3Eby%20integrating%20climate%20risk%20management%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20its%20provisions.%20The%20government%20should%20ideally%20increase%20budgetary%20allocations%20for%20MGNREGS%20considering%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fopinion%2Fbudget-2023-loosen-purse-strings-for-mgnrega-it-aids-in-climate-change-adaptation-9963371.html%5C%22%3E65%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20allocated%20budget%20to%20MGNREGA%20goes%20into%20natural%20resource%20and%20water%20management%2C%20drought%20proofing%2C%20and%20securing%20the%20livelihood%20of%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20marginalised.%20But%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20programme%20has%20seen%20drastic%20cuts%20in%20budgetary%20allocations%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F03131216%2FScreen-Shot-2021-11-03-at-1.07.58-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221085%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F03131216%2FScreen-Shot-2021-11-03-at-1.07.58-PM.png%201085w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F03131216%2FScreen-Shot-2021-11-03-at-1.07.58-PM-300x172.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F03131216%2FScreen-Shot-2021-11-03-at-1.07.58-PM-1024x586.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-562199%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20nevil%20zaveri%2FFlickr%20(CC%20BY%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%20as%20decision%20makers%3A%20The%20levers%20of%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20women-led%20development%20paradigm%20must%20ensure%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20at%20all%20levels%20of%20governance%2C%20both%20local%20and%20national.%20Since%20women%20face%20higher%20risks%20and%20greater%20burdens%20from%20the%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20their%20involvement%20in%20climate%20change-related%20decision-making%20becomes%20crucial%20for%20the%20success%20of%20climate%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unwomen.org%2Fen%2Fnews-stories%2Fexplainer%2F2022%2F03%2Fexplainer-why-women-need-to-be-at-the-heart-of-climate-action%5C%22%3EStudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20shown%20that%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation%20in%20national%20parliaments%20has%20resulted%20in%20lower%20emissions%20through%20a%20stringent%20adoption%20of%20climate%20change%20policies.%20Unfortunately%2C%20India%20is%20among%20the%20bottom%2025%25%20of%20countries%20with%20only%2015.2%25%20of%20representation%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20as%20shown%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fpolitics%2Fwomens-reservation-how-india-stacks-up-against-the-world-in-charts-11695115774190.html%5C%22%3Erecent%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Inter-Parliamentary%20Union%20(IPU)%20data.%20Increasing%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation%20to%2033%25%20can%20improve%20India%E2%80%99s%20relative%20ranking%20globally%20from%20the%20current%20141%3Cspan%3Est%3C%2Fspan%3E%20rank%20to%2054%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%C2%A0rank%20among%20185%20countries%20covered%20in%20the%20IPU.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20conclude%2C%20we%20argue%20that%20much%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20in%20the%20area%20of%20climate%20action%20using%20a%20gender-inclusive%20lens.%20This%20should%20not%20be%20limited%20to%20articulating%20goals%20on%20climate%20change%20mitigation%20and%20adaptation%20but%20must%20also%20focus%20on%20redressing%20the%20adverse%20impact%20of%20climate%20change%20that%20is%20already%20playing%20out%20in%20the%20lives%20and%20livelihoods%20of%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDivya%20Pradeep%20and%20K.C.%20Adaina%20teach%20Economics%20at%20Christ%20University%20and%20Azim%20Premji%20University%2C%20Bangalore%20respectively.%3C%2Fem%