ll-businesses-whats-different-this-round-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPPP%20loan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20April%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20online%20short-term%20lending%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.ilnd.445392%2Fgov.uscourts.ilnd.445392.1.0.pdf%3Futm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20a%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20September%2015%20in%20the%20US%20District%20Court%20in%20Illinois'%20Southern%20Division%2C%20saying%20the%20COVID%20relief%20program%20erroneously%20rejected%20their%20application%20for%20loan%20forgiveness%2C%20according%20to%20the%20document%20first%20reported%20by%20Seamus%20Hughes's%20CourtWatch%20newsletter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreditNinja%20was%20recently%20found%20to%20have%20given%20short-term%20and%20high-cost%20loans%20with%20interest%20rates%20as%20high%20as%20447%25%20in%20Texas%2C%20taking%20advantage%20of%20a%20loophole%20by%20registering%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcredit%20access%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20a%20broker%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.khou.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Finvestigations%2Fhigh-interest-loans-legal-texas%2F285-39fd51eb-131a-4506-bdc5-6809f3ddd8d9%3Futm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20investigation%20by%20KHOU-11.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20denial%2C%20the%20SBA%20said%20CreditNinja%20wasn't%20eligible%20for%20the%20loan%20forgiveness%20program%20because%20it's%20a%20lending%20company%20%E2%80%94%20a%20type%20of%20company%20that%20has%20been%20excluded%20from%20receiving%20loans%20from%20the%20Small%20Business%20Association%20under%20the%20group's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.cornell.edu%2Fcfr%2Ftext%2F13%2F120.110%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1996%20Rules%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20CreditNinja%20claims%20in%20its%20complaint%20that%20those%20rules%20were%20never%20mentioned%20in%20the