nsitive%20cases%20for%20the%20FBI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disgraced%20FBI%20special%20agent%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20one%20count%20of%20concealment%20of%20material%20facts%20as%20part%20of%20a%20deal%20with%20federal%20prosecutors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcGonigal%20has%20now%20admitted%20both%20to%20illicitly%20working%20for%20Oleg%20Deripaska%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sanctioned%20Russian%20oligarch%20with%20longstanding%20ties%20to%20Vladimir%20Putin%20%E2%80%94%20after%20leaving%20the%20FBI.%20He%20has%20also%20admitted%20to%20taking%20cash%20payments%20and%20undertaking%20private%20business%20development%20efforts%20in%20Albania%20while%20he%20was%20still%20in%20a%20senior%20position%20at%20the%20FBI's%20New%C2%A0%20York%20Field%20Office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20remains%20unclear%20is%20whether%20McGonigal%20and%20Deripaska%20had%20any%20contact%20while%20McGonigal%20was%20still%20employed%20by%20the%20bureau.%20The%20FBI's%20investigation%20began%20after%20British%20authorities%20learned%20that%20McGonigal%20was%20secrety%20meeting%20with%20a%20Russian%20oligarch%20in%20London%20in%202018%2C%20the%20same%20year%20he%20retired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%20on%20Friday%2C%20McGonigal%20said%20that%20the%20%24225%2C000%20was%20lent%20to%20him%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Bfriend%20and%20prospective%20business%20partner%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20money%20was%20intended%20to%20help%20start%20a%20business%20that%20he%20was%20setting%20up%20without%20the%20FBI's%20knowledge%20while%20still%20working%20for%20the%20bureau.%20That%20individual%20has%20been%20identified%20by%20several%20news%20outlets%20as%20Agron%20Neza%2C%20a%20former%20Albanian%20intelligence%20official%20who%20now%20lives%20in%20New%20Jersey.%20Neza's%20loan%20to%20McGonigal%2C%20delivered%20in%20three%20cash%20payments%2C%20had%20no%20written%20terms%20and%20was%20never%20paid%20back.%20McGonigal's%20former%20girlfriend%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharles-mcgonigal-fbi-indictment-allison-guerriero-russia-deripaska-spies-nypd-giuliani-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20observed%20some%20of%20the%20cash%20in%20a%20bag%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20their%20Brooklyn%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20money%20had%20%26quot%3Bno%20conditions%20or%20strings%20attached%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20words%20of%20Judge%20Colleen%20Kollar-Kotelly.%20According%20to%20a%20statement%20of%20the%20offense%2C%20the%20money%20was%20connected%20to%20a%20web%20of%20relationships%20he%20developed%20with%20Albanian%20officials%2C%20including%20Prime%20Minister%20Edi%20Rama.%20McGonigal%20agreed%20that%20he%20had%20counseled%20Rama%20to%20avoid%20awarding%20state%20energy%20contracts%20to%20Russian%20companies%2C%20advice%20that%20benefited%20another%20Albanian%20official%20who%20was%20working%20for%20Rama%20as%20an%20informal%20advisor%20even%20as%20he%20consulted%20for%20a%20Chinese%20energy%20company.%20That%20official%20was%20to%20the%20friend%20who%20had%20lent%20McGonigal%20the%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%2C%20McGonigal%20described%20this%20conflicted%20intermingling%20of%20public%20and%20private%20interest%20as%20his%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20business%20development%20efforts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeth%20DuCharme%2C%20one%20of%20McGonigal's%20attorneys%2C%20told%20reporters%20outside%20the%20courthouse%20that%20his%20client%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Bhit%20the%20ground%20running%26quot%3B%20with%20his%20business%20efforts%20after%20retiring%20from%20the%20bureau%20in%20September%202018.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcGonigal%20was%20indicted%20twice%20in%20January%20%E2%80%94%20once%20in%20Washington%20DC%20and%20also%20in%20New%20York%20%E2%80%94%20after%20a%20grand%20jury%20investigated%20the%20ex-counterintelligence%20chief.%20Insider%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexclusive-fbi-charles-mcgonigal-trump-russia-grand-jury-oleg-deripaska-202